 presented on financial topics at the university of chicago the new york society of securities analysts the cboe risk management conference and risk institute in  he was invited and appeared as the first derivatives panelist at the barrons art of successful investing conference dean holds an mba in analytical finance with highest honors from the university of chicago where he received the citibank award for best performance in finance he received a bachelor of arts magna cum laude from st johns university he lives in new york city with his wife and two sons and daughter brian bier brian bier is a managing director and head of equity derivative sales and trading for macro risk advisors brian leads the sales and execution team utilizing his expertise in option analytics and deep understanding of risk relationships to deliver superior pricing and advisory services to mra clients prior to joining mra brian was head of listed equity derivative trading at nomura securities overseeing all single stock and indexetf derivative products he previously ran energy retail and technology volatility trading books at banc of america securities brian began his career at lehman brothers where he was a structured equity derivatives trader brian holds a bachelor of science in operations research from cornell university where he graduated magna cum laude and was class valedictorian he resides in westchester with his wife and two young children pravit chintawongvanich pravit chintawongvanich is the head of derivatives strategy at macro risk advisors pravit publishes a daily strategy note focusing on global macro and crossasset volatility especially as it relates to the equity derivatives markets and equity index volatility the daily note covers a wide range of topics including tactical options trade ideas market analysis  commentary and higherlevel discussion of options strategies pravit is a regular guest on bloomberg tv and cnbc and his work is frequently cited in bloomberg ft and the wall street journal pravit leads the derivatives strategy team which works with clients on bespoke derivatives solutions including strategy backtests options trade construction and volatility screens before joining mra pravit worked in equity derivatives trading and risk management at rbc capital markets pravit has a bachelor of science degree in electrical engineering from new mexico state university and a master in mathematical finance degree from the university of toronto     brian connors brian connors is an institutional salestrader at macro risk advisors brian brings to the team experience in cash equity trading allowing mra to offer greater coverage in this area he was formerly of janney capital markets where he worked as a senior salesperson and trader on the cash equity desk providing lead coverage to mostly equity longshort hedge funds  brian graduated from uncchapel hill where he earned a ba with a concentration in finance and management  he was also a four year scholarship member of the men’s lacrosse team  brian currently resides in manhattan jerry hammerschmidt jerry hammerschmidt is an institutional salestrader at macro risk advisors jerry brings over  years of sales trading and derivatives experience to mra he will provide strategy and execution services across single stock and index options jerry began his career at morgan stanley trading options on the floor of the hang seng option and futures exchange and held multiple positions within the equity division at the investment bank in asia and new york following his time at ms jerry worked for several years at barclays where he was a director of otc equity derivatives sales he most recently worked at societe generale in the equity derivatives group  jerry attended florida state university where he studied economics he resides in armonk with his wife and three children  chris kettenmann chris kettenmann is chief energy strategist at macro risk advisors in this role chris generates institutional commenta